Nortal is helping to build a next generation Cognitive City in the Middle East - a seamless AI-orchestrated metropolis, home and workplace for more than a million citizens from around the world. Did we catch your attention?

We’re looking for a Product Lead to drive building a Super App. Think one app with 50 mini apps, an aggregator of services and sectors with a marketplace on top of it. Your mission is to help build a team with research, design, business development and operations, as well as help imagine what the Super App could be.

The Product Lead will be part of a dedicated team that operates semi-independently within Nortal, and is responsible for exploration of opportunity spaces via Mobile apps. The Product Lead will help drive strategy development, opportunity sizing, experimentation and KPI definition, and work with a team of Product Managers to bring the opportunity to life.

What You Will Be Doing

Develop the Super App from 0 to 1, take the high-level vision into product strategy and roadmap;
Engage with C-level stakeholders to help them shape the idea and bring those forward not just into tangible product but into a whole product ecosystem;
Identify new users/user needs/market opportunities/service ideas, and help define strategies that solve for these;
Leverage various methodologies (design thinking, experimentation, etc) to validate assumptions quickly, using the insights to drive iterations of the strategy;
Define KPIs to measure product success;
As a result, you and your team's work will set the foundations for the greenfield Cognitive City.


What You Will Need

You have 8+ years of experience building ventures and digital products like marketplaces, aggregators and Super Apps, ideally in high paced start-up environments;
You are comfortable with a big vision, lots of ambiguity and shifting priorities;
You know how to find a balance between blue sky thinking and ideation, to tactical delivery needs;
You can bring product vision to customer to shape the conversation and sell the product before it has requirements;
You have strong empathy for customers and can identify their current and future needs.
Willingness to travel 10-20% of the time to the Middle East, where you will be able to interact with end users directly.


Heleen Anderson

Role Descriptions:

Data Privacy Officers (DPOs) are typically responsible for ensuring HSBC meets its obligations under data protection and privacy laws within their particular jurisdiction. They may provide expert advice, guidance and direction and support the necessary standards and controls to enable the Bank, including its employees and relevant third parties, to manage privacy risks and comply with . obligations under data protection laws in relation to the processing of personal data.




Job Description:




Provide commercially aware privacy advice aligned with financial services best practices.

• Interpret and oversee the implementation of HSBC Group approved risk appetite into local policies, processes, systems, models and limits.

• Lead the design, development and renewal of data protection and privacy risk policy and minimum standards with regular engagement of Chief Risk Officer, business leaders, and within local legal, ensuring alignment with regulatory requirements and responding to ongoing change in the business and external environment.

• Provide advice on privacy requirements to help build privacy by design and privacy by default into processing activities involving personal data.

• Provide advice and guidance on all aspects of data protection and privacy risk including the records required to demonstrate compliance, risk identification, assessment, mitigation, response and reporting.

• Provide informed recommendations for risk mitigation and supporting action plans for development and realization.

• Provide advice and guidance on the appointment and use of third parties and support appropriate due diligence and advice on the necessary contractual arrangements (including compliant data processing agreements) that need to be in place with third parties processing personal data on behalf of HSBC.

• Provide incident management advice and/or support as needed and ensure that data incidents and breaches are responded to and managed effectively with data subjects and that the relevant authorities are informed within necessary timeframes.

• Ensure privacy programme processes and procedures are established and adhered to across your jurisdiction and local offices.

• Maintain, support and review procedures to enable data subjects to exercise their individual rights.

• Provide support and guidance to HSBC as directed by Chief Risk Officer or regional Data Privacy lead in providing advice related to Data Privacy and Information Governance, including matters that are complex or have potential for significant legal, financial and / or reputational impact, with a particular focus on, and responsibility for, DPO activities within jurisdiction.

INTERNAL

• Ensure the company delivers on day-to-day operational work such as the fulfilment of DSARs and DPIAs.

• Maintain responsibility, as directed by the Chief Risk Officer, for the execution of business and operational strategies related to DPO activities within jurisdiction.

• Provide advice relating to Data Privacy and Information Governance issues involving the relevant jurisdiction, with a particular focus on, and responsibility for, DPO activities including developing strategies to respond to changes in law and regulation.

• Maintain audit compliance with data protection law




Qualifications:




Maintain an expert knowledge of data protection legislation, regulations and best practices, particularly in the financial sector;

• Monitor HSBC’s compliance with applicable regulatory requirements and data protection laws;

• Monitoring compliance with country and entity specific data privacy laws, with any other data privacy provisions and with HSBC Group policies and FIMS relating to the protection of personal data, including the assignment of responsibilities, awareness-raising and staff training, and the related audits;

• Maintain a strong knowledge of regulatory frameworks, risk treatment and mitigation strategies;

• Provide leadership and strategic data protection guidance and advice to ensure HSBC’s strategy is aligned to privacy requirements;

• Understand key risk indicators and define privacy metrics to identify privacy risks and issues that affect HSBC.




Experience:

• Comprehensive knowledge and experience of Data Privacy and Information Governance and a working knowledge of the laws in the major jurisdictions in which HSBC operates;

• Recognised as a subject matter expert;

• A relevant data protection or privacy certification such as CIPP (preferred);

• Corporate experience and Compliance experience an advantage, but not essential;

• Detailed knowledge of the HSBC Group corporate structures, its business and personnel and a clear understanding of HSBC’s corporate culture;

• Strong ability to priorities;

• Strong communication and inter-personal skills;

• Proven ability to establish and maintain a high degree of confidentiality, respect, trust and credibility at all levels;

• Experience in communicating, interacting and maintaining good working relationships with supervisory authorities;

• Strong written and verbal communication skills;

• Well-developed and professional interpersonal skills; ability to interact effectively with people at all organisational levels;

• Ability to work unsupervised, exercise leadership and influence change;

• Ability to use independent judgement and discretion when making the majority of decisions;

• Detail-focused approach needed to recommend and implement strategic improvements on a range of data privacy and data protection issues

At Vertiv, we build products that keep critical technologies running 24/7. We are proud we were the first to protect mainframes with precision cooling systems. We were the first to introduce an integrated enclosure system to distributed networks. We help some of the largest names in the industry bring new capacity online faster and at a lower cost when search and social media increased demand for storage and computing. Our portfolio spans power, thermal and infrastructure management products, software and solutions, and is complemented by a network of nearly 250 service centers worldwide.




We are now looking for a Firmware Engineer to join our team in Zagreb, Croatia.

This is an on-site role and we are offering a relocation package.




As a Firmware Engineer, you will drive the product development process from beginning to end. This role will focus on Single Phase UPS products. The Firmware Engineer will review market requirements documents and create engineer requirement specifications, provide feedback to different function team, design the logic and algorithms code, debug the code, solve the test issue and market issue.




Your main responsibilities as a Firmware Engineer will be to:




Deliver high-quality C/C++ code in a real-time embedded environment;
Specify, design, and implement functionality and behaviors of embedded subsystems;
Design the software architecture and firmware implementation on hardware through integration, test, and high-volume manufacturing;
Responsible for all aspects of firmware design and development for new innovative products and features using embedded microprocessors;
Participates in sustaining activities for existing products including diagnosis and resolution of defects;
Interact with engineering, marketing, management, and project leads to assure that product development priorities are completed to schedule and budget while ensuring quality and product performance requirements are met;
Responsible for keeping excellent, organized project records and documentation;
Product development activities include design and development, design reviews, documentation, product verification, coordination with quality assurance, and field validation.




In order to be successful in this role, you will need to have:

BS or above in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Computer Science or the equivalent in experience with evidence of exceptional ability;
Fluent in software fundamentals including software design and maintainability;
Strong development skills in C/C++, familiar with the development environment;
Familiar with control theory and digital signal processing;
Possess good mathematical foundation, with strong research willingness and ability;
Integration, troubleshooting, and debugging skills;
Excellent team working skills, drive, self-motivation, and focus on results;
Experience in version control and bug tracking;
Ability to collaborate and communicate complex technical concepts;
Experience of version control and bug tracking;
Experience in UPS and power module development is preferred.




If YOU are the person we are looking for, feel free to apply and let's start drafting your future career in a healthy and growing environment!

Basic Function

The Geo-Consulting Manager would be responsible for leading and growing the Geo-Consulting practice, providing quality advisory support to the organization and reporting deliverables.

Key Accountabilities

Work closely with the Commercial team and Service Line Managers (locally and in the region as required) to develop Fugro activities and long-term relations with Clients;
Review project requirements, prepare proposals or provide advice on proposal preparation by the commercial team on large projects;
Develop innovative approaches and value propositions to address client challenges, positioning Fugro as a preferred contractor/supplier with a strong understanding of the competition;
Grow team and geo-consulting activities, deliver unbiased advice to address client problems by combining Fugro’s multiple services. Key KPIs are geo-consulting profitability and client satisfaction;
Ensure quality of geotechnical deliverables, with the support of a Geo-Science Manager responsible for day-to-day activities and coordination of geologists;
Supervise Junior grade team members on projects and direct implementation of appropriate techniques. Resolve and perform independently complex engineering assignments with innovative solutions. Supervises moderate to complex field investigations, and assists Junior level professionals in the completion of assignments;
Show initiative as part of the role in all duties and set an example as necessary for the team members;
Establish and maintain long-term relations with clients and business partners. Identify and develop engineering and geo-consulting service opportunities with clients;
Promote development of expertise by suggesting and contributing to internal innovation projects, preparation of technical publications, and delivering presentations at relevant industry events;
Be updated with and actively contribute to the implementation of published Quality Assurance, Health, Safety and Environmental procedures in the workplace


Qualifications / Skills / Experience Required

Master’s Degree or higher education in Civil Engineering or Geotechnical Engineering;
Minimum 10+ years of practical experience in a similar role;
Self-motivated, pro-active, committed and flexible with strong problem-solving skills;
Good Commercial understanding and capable of developing innovative solutions;
Willing to travel to and work at the site if necessary and work effectively in a multi-cultural environment.


Role Specific Technical Competencies Required

Consult extensively with a high degree of reliance placed on scientific interpretations and advice;
Direct team members or individuals assisting on projects. Mentor performance excellence and adherence to quality standards;
Knowledge of site characterization techniques and geotechnical interpretation work, environment and water management (surface and resource), monitoring program, and big data management;
Experience with soil and rock mechanics, and geotechnical engineering principles;
Stay abreast of current professional standards, periodicals, and technological advancements. Maintain meaningful involvement in professional organizations (Chartership, Professional Engineers);
Detailed experience with computational geotechnics packages (Plaxis, FLAC), excel spreadsheets and exposure, 3D modelling (Leapfrog/Micromine), and GIS (ArcGIS/QGIS). Exposure to VBA/Python programming and geotechnical monitoring works is preferred.


Role Specific Behavioural Competencies Required

Problem-solving/Judgment the ability to observe, think critically and to solve problems using data, analysis, interpretation, and reasoning skills;
Teamwork the proven dedication and ability to work successfully with others, adding value to the team. Share knowledge, develop new competences and coach junior personnel on assigned projects, proposals;
Information and Communication Communicates appropriately and effectively with a range of people on a variety of subjects in order to inform, educate or influence them. Processes and provides data / information to meet business requirements;
Client Focus the ability to identify, meet and sometimes exceed the needs and expectations of (external or internal) clients, resulting in (long-term) client satisfaction. Develop innovative approach to solving client challenges and materialise value proposition;
Planning & Organizing able to set priorities and determine actions, time and resources (tools, software, people, and budget as appropriate.) to achieve pre-defined goals. Monitor and manage timely delivery, leading to reliability and client satisfaction.


Disclaimer For Recruitment Agencies

Fugro does not accept any unsolicited applications from recruitment agencies. Acquisition to Fugro Recruitment or any Fugro employee is not appreciated.

